If you are unable to log in on Twitter now, chill, you are not the only. It is not clear what caused the worldwide outage. According to The Gamer, Website Downdector has reportedly seen a huge increase in the number of Twitter users claiming that they were not able to access the site. “Downdetector, which tracks outages by collating status reports from a number of sources, showed more than 12,000 outage reports in the United States,” Reuters reported. It is reported that users from the United Kingdom, Mexico, Brazil and Italy also facing the outage. Update: The site is back online, Twitter is yet to issue communication regarding the outage. 